post_text:
Game changing air filtration system coming to Southern Wells for school opening! The School Board approved the purchase on Tuesday night.

This new technology removes particulates (like dust, dander, pollen), pathogens, viruses and bacteria, along with volatile organic compounds and odors. Students and staff WILL notice a difference in the air quality!

This is in addition to the NEW HVAC air conditioning/heating in the elementary for this year. Great investments for the health of students and staff. See attached! #RAIDERPRIDE

post_text:
This just in from our good friends at Rose-Hulman:

Rose-Hulman’s AskRose Homework Help has added daytime hours to help homebound students better understand math and science homework problems from their virtual or online classes during the current coronavirus public health crisis that has led to many schools moving to an e-learning environment.

Free homework help is now available Monday through Friday from noon to 3 p.m. (Eastern Standard Time) by a phone call, email or chat session. Our traditional hours remain unchanged: Sunday through Thursday from 7-10 p.m. (Eastern Standard Time.)

Students may call 877-ASK-ROSE (877-275-7673) or email and chat on our AskRose website, AskRose.org. The site also offers more than 500 resources available through videos and downloadable reference materials.

Rose-Hulman students also are doing remote learning but are able to continue offering this service from locations throughout the country.

Need help students? Give them a call!

post_text:
Job Posting
Custodian 3rd shift: To provide students and staff with a safe, attractive, comfortable, clean, healthy and efficient place in which to learn, play and develop. To perform routine custodial activities at an assigned school site or facility. Clean classrooms and related facilities as assigned; cleans furniture, walls, floors, and ceilings. Maintain buildings, assigned area and adjacent ground areas in a clean, orderly and secure condition. Reports safety, sanitary, and fire hazards to appropriate authority and recommend needs for maintenance repairs. High school diploma or equivalent. Physical condition allows the lifting of heavy loads, including lifting tables, chairs, and moving of furniture. Pay rate is $17.02/hour with benefits available. Hours are 11 pm – 7:30 am. Background check required. Please email applications to rking@swraiders.com or drop off at central office use door #1.

post_text:
National statistics are staggering:
Half of students report being cyberbullied.
Cyberbullying makes a student 9 times more likely to consider suicide,
Suicide is the second leading cause of death for young people aged 10 to 24.

Southern Wells Community Schools will implement a new technology solution for suicide prevention and potential cyberbullying over the weekend. All online activity of students that is currently filtered for inappropriate use will also be filtered for suicide, harmful behaviors to self or others, and cyberbullying. This new feature is state-of-the-art technology used by the school district in effort to keep our students (and staff) safer. Building administration will be alerted to online searches or comments made to students or by students that reference harm to themselves or others so help can be on its way. See this link for more information from our software vendor: https://www.lightspeedsystems.com/protect/

post_text:
Work progress continues on the many construction projects at Southern Wells Community Schools! THANK YOU TAXPAYERS for supporting these projects!

New concrete is being poured at the football stadium for better accessibility, classrooms and HS main office taking shape, NEW signage for the buildings. The IMPROVED learning spaces are going to be fantastic for students!

First student day is less than a month away: August 9. Calling ALL RAIDERS!

post_text: PROGRESS! Thanks to Shawnee Construction for their work done to date! Learning spaces are starting to return with ceiling grids in classrooms; HVAC air units going up for fresh, conditioned air for students, old chillers are gone to open the entrance up for students to/from the agriculture building; administrative office space being redesigned for efficient student service. Raider Pride!

post_text: Construction is underway at Southern Wells Community Schools! Making way for a new air conditioning/heating system and roof in the jr-sr high school, total refresh of the jr-sr high school office, and new sewage piping underneath the elementary library! Students WILL notice a difference in August! Look for a new, improved learning environment for 2019-20.

post_text:
Due to Construction Activities in the High School, the office has moved and will operate out of the elementary school building. All High School office members can be reached by calling 765-728-2121 Ext. 2073.
Appointments will be reached by entering the elementary at exterior door #26 on the west side of the building.
Summer school classes will also be held in the elementary building this year and students should enter at door #26.

post_text: How COOL for Southern Wells Community Schools students!! Students were able to explore vehicles and talk with representatives from Liberty Township Fire, Chester Township Fire, Wells County EMS, Wells County Sheriff's Office, and Luthern Air. How many times do you get to sit in a helicopter?? Only at Southern Wells Community Schools! Thank you to our friends at law enforcement, fire departments, EMS, and Lutheran Air for making the last student day a MEMORABLE and SUCCESSFUL experience for students!

post_text:
We are pleased to announce the hire of Alexis Howell, a recent graduate of The Ohio State University, as our new Agriculture teacher and FFA sponsor for the 2019-2020 school year. She will begin working with students before the conclusion of this school year and taking over full responsibilities for the programs this summer.
Welcome Ms. Howell!

post_text: Congratulations to our young artists recognized during student spotlight on success at Thursday's School Board meeting! Other students recognized, but not present, included Isabelle Harlan and Gracie Shope. Congratulations to all our Raiders!

post_text: The Southern Wells School Board voted March 14 to add four staff inservice dates to the 2019-2020 calendar. These will be one-hour delays for students on Wednesday mornings on November 6, January 8, March 4 and May 6. If a two-hour delay would happen to occur on those dates, there would be no impact on the students. No other change was made to the calendar.
